<section class="section">

<h2>
Research <span>Overview</span>
</h2>

<p>
Non-coding RNAs are central regulators of cellular identity, gene expression, development, and disease. They include long non-coding RNAs, microRNAs, circular RNAs, small regulatory RNAs, and other RNA species that influence transcriptional, post-transcriptional, and epigenetic regulation.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, non-coding RNA is presented as a major transcriptomic research area: a regulatory layer connecting genome function, epigenomics, RNA expression, cancer biology, biomarker discovery, and precision medicine.
</p>

</section>

